Surely a place worth trying, the food is great and fresh, the pricing is reasonable and it is always clean in here. Keep up the good work.
Food is delicious and the lady who helped us was great as well.
Had a great experience in this spot with my girlfriend. The food comes out rapidly and the service is just fantastic. Prices are reasonable.
The best soul food ever, me and my family came here and absolutely loved it definitely recommend

Had a super weird experience here. I stopped here on my way back from a walk with my pup. I tied my pup to the fence outside and went in to get a sandwich and use the rest room. When i got out of the rest room the owner of the restaurant locked the door and would not let me go out! He kept saying that my dog broke the fence and I need to pay for it. 1. My dog did not break the fence. He is very calm and does not pull. 2. The fence is DC city property and not the restaurant's. I felt unsafe and attacked. I am a good person so I still paid for my sandwich. I will NOT go back.
Awesome place to eat

(Translated by Google) Rich flavor, the quantity of the dishes is good, the attention of the staff is great, very friendly, they help and guide tourists with honesty and joy, the price of the dishes is accessible, clean place, I recommend it.  (Original) Rico sabor, la cantidad de los platos es buena, la atencion del personal es genial muy amigables, ayudan y orientan a los turistas con honestidad y alegria, el precio de los platos es accesible, lugar limpio, lo recomiendo.

It seems under new ownership there is a significant decrease in portion size. Wings tasted different so did the cornbread. Was still good but overall disappointed that it was not the same experience as before.

The new owner was nice however the food is not quality.  I ordered two rib platters the baked beans were burnt and the macaroni and cheese taste like it had sliced cheese just microwaved on top.  I spent over $40 and did not eat my meal.  This was a horrible experience for Super bowl Sunday!  I will not be going back!  Definitely not the same macaroni & cheese or baked beans I'm seeing in the google photos from a few months ago.  Sad they have to do better!
The food was alright. But to expensive.
Best ribs in town.
It was ok good potatoe salad  ribs could  be larger
Great patio and pretty good BBQ. I've had better but it's a great spot in the Capitol Hill area.

I’m sorry to see that this place is closed for now. I’ve been so disappointed in DMV barbecue since moving from the south, and this was the best I’ve had yet. Every place seems to try to go over the top with unique recipes and additions, good BBQ should keep it simple. The patio and environment was super cute and comfortable, and the family were beyond friendly and accommodating. I didn’t expect to be actually “served” when I grabbed a seat after placing our window order. So so kind! I can’t wait to return and will keep an eye for them to re-open.
Yummy BBQ, currently closed for renovation.
Kenny ain't playing no games. So good

Was looking for a good BBQ spot for being in town for a few days. I really liked the patio of this place and how it's nestled into the neighborhood  That said, the beef brisket sandwich I got was good, but nothing too extraordinary. Likewise with sides. Feels like flavor is a little lacking  Customer service was excellent though. One of the cooks was on a smoke break and saw me swatting at mosquitoes and tossed me his spray. Cool move. Will return next time in DC
Bbq ppulled pork sandwich was delicious

Kenny's has great service, hospitality, and of course, delicious choices from brisket that melts in your mouth to perfectly softened collard greens. I love what they've done with the interior and patio seating.  Even during this pandemic, you can see regulars coming by to say hello and grab some goods to go. Can't wait to come back.
Great pulled pork and corn bread! Lovely owners, a great local place to support during the pandemic.
The food had no seasoning, no flavor,  and just didn’t taste like the Kenny’s Smoke House that I’m accustomed to eating.  Hated it!!!!!!!!!!!!!!😩
Amazing food and amazing customer service! They have the greatest briskets and the chicken wings. Definitely coming back millions of times :)

Very comfortable outdoor seating area, which was perfect for me and a few of my friends. The food was incredibly tasty! It was also served in a timely manner. We will be coming back again for sure. I highly recommend the brisket platter with onions rings!
East meets West: delicious American barbecue and authentic Korean home cooking. Great comfort food. Excellent for family meals.
Great brisket and ribs
SO GOOD!  I needed some comfort food today and Kenny's delivered BIG! Beans delicious, greens outstanding, chicken rocked.  Thank you!

I admire this restaurant! They serve awesome dishes, their menu is rich, The cook in that place is very experienced, I enjoy a lot tasting all their food. The dishes are consistently of high class, the attitude towards the customers  is agreeable. I visit often this place and I was never discontended. I recommend it with no hesitation.
For the most part the food was good. Nothing different than other places. Large serving sizes. Nice customer service
Great food great portions! 2nd time going. Make sure it's the one in NE!
Food is good

A friend told me to venture out to DC for some BBQ and never tried this place. So glad I did! Smoked meats here are just different. Sauces are rich, cuts are thick, and the smoker keeps the meats moist with plenty of flavor. My friends and I decided to order the pulled pork, brisket, pork ribs and the slow smoked wing with a side of fries, coleslaw and onion rings. The brisket had to be my favorite. It was so delicious and I found myself taking a break after each bite to enjoy it. The slides are no joke. The onion rings were fried perfectly and they made the coleslaw just the way I like it. Cold in temp, crispy cabbage and plenty of mayo. Highly recommend this location if you want some quality bbq. They take Covid seriously with ordering through the window and outside patio seating. Food made take some time to come out, but well worth the wait.
Food and service was great

I ordered the 4pc beef ribs with Mac and cheese. Let me start by saying that I’ve eaten here before and it was pretty decent. However, not this time around. The ribs were tough and did not taste fresh, the Mac and cheese was awful to say the least. It lacked major seasoning sad sad!!! The only thing I can say was really good was their BBQ sauce. This meal wasn’t worth $25 plus the tip!!!!!

Despite the heat and the social-distancing, our family had a very enjoyable time! The pork ribs and coleslaw combination is a must but they do have a wide variety of other sides. The service was phenomenal and we would definitely visit again!
The food is delicious and the staff are friendly.  Especially, the grape vine planted on the terrace is beautiful.  The lunch sitting on the patio is fantastic.

I visited dc from nyc for a work. And i came across this beautiful bbq shop near union station. First of all food was on point probably best ribs i ever had in my life. Owner (ms. Lee) was so nice to me and asked me if i needed anything extra such as sauces and napkins. This place got a beautiful patio outside to take out and dine in. I am definitely coming back to this restaurant when im in Dc.  Loved it
The food was not very tasty to me. The food tasted more baked than barbecued, and the ribs were tough.

Kenny's is easily now one of my favorite joints in the city! It's a family owned and operated establishment, they put tons of thought and care into how they run their business. They have this spicy bbq sauce they got in from Texas that is just fantastic. I went with a buddy and we both had a platter of food that could've easily fed ten people haha ribs, pulled pork, fried fish, baked beans, mac and cheese, collard greens, cornbread, slaw, french fries, and onion rings. Literally everything was mouth watering delicious. Ribs fell off the bone, there pulled pork was tender and juicy, the fish was flavorful and had a nice crispy fried coating. The owner that we meet, Summer, is definitely one of those businesswoman who could be doing anything and would be killer successful at it bc she clearly has a vision for how she runs her business, and we're glad this place has her behind the helm. Their fried fish is second only to Oohhs and Aahhs, in my opinion, and their ribs rival DCity Smokehouse. I'll be coming back for sure, and it's great that they've made all the precautions for social distancing to safely enjoy the foodie experience. five stars!
I wish I could give a ZERO star rating!! The food is HORRIBLE!! The service is TERRIBLE!! The cost is way OVERPRICED!! WARNING!!  STAY AWAY!!
The food & service at this place was completely AWFUL!! Also, the menu items are not available, as advertised. The only positive is the nice location.
I am a fan of BBQ / this place is decent
They didn't have anymore ribs the greens taste like seafood
The place offers a vast variety of delicious food. I enjoy eating here. The employees are always super friendly, prices are fair and the place is always neat.

Was walking by Kenny’s last week while walking my dog and I noticed that they’re re-opened for take out! I finally got my brisket sandwich... it was so juicy and tender just like before 😋😋😋 They are open everyday besides Mondays. And they now use the side patio to pick up/order your food through a sliding window!!

Glad I discovered this little smoke house in Washington. I ate there twice and god it was good ! Ribs, wings, brisket, everything was great ! And the homemade sauces are just delicious ! The waitress is sooooo nice, we had a good talk ! Next time i'm in D.C, i'm definitely coming back ! Can't wait !
The meat is great!
This is my go-to place for the best brisket in town. I’m also crazy for the bulgogi. The atmosphere is wonderful. Music is perfect and the service is great. Highly recommend!
The food at Kenny’s was so good  I had the fried fish platter with fries  ,coleslaw cornbread and my favorite  Joe’s peach tea I tried almost everything their. Delicious

We where in DC over the weekend and went to this place lady at counter was very pleasant, I can't say the same about the meal that we had mac was ok, greens ok ,fish so so ,rib chewy, chicken was probably a day old or so,pulled pork was chewy, beans couldn't eat,and so on would not be going back!!!!!
Wonderful food and staff. Has a beautiful patio space and is dog friendly!
They provide the biggest portions for the least money.

We had a fantastic time in this place. We liked the amazing vibes and the menu. The waiters are super amiable. I am glad we finally managed to eat here.

Good spot for fast lunch  Hog Kenny's BBQ Smokehouse  is a fast food restaurant that serves BBQ.  They have a drive through, inside dining, or you can get your order to go.  The restaurant is clean and the staff is welcoming and accommodating.  Kenny's BBQ Smokehouse offers  a variety of BBQ along with sides, soft drinks, beer and cobler.  On this visit I ordered the  combination plate with brisket, pork ribs, fries, and beans
I love bbq but this is not my place the mac& cheese was bland and the potato salad was dry sorry I won't be eating there anymore

Kenny's never disappoints. Been eating here for years. One of the best BBQ places in D.C. A little disappointed you moved your BBQ sauces behind the counter though. Bring them back out front so we can enjoy them all again!
Great barbeque! Meat is tender and delicious! Staff is friendly!

Always a GREAT EXPERIENCE. Lunch or Dinner is always Great.  The two Young Ladies work their are always nice and very professional at all times.  Great Dining area. Great music. And a lot fun with friends, Family or co-workers. Anytime is the best times at Kenny’s. THE FOOD IS GREAT.!!!!!!!!!!!
This place is great! Affordable pricing, big dishes and the staff are regularly very friendly.
Superb! The food is wonderful.

Wonderful service (super kind staff), the Mac-and-cheese and the sweet yams were delicious! Plentiful outdoor seating. The ribs were just okay, which knocks this review down a star. They were overcooked and the meat was tough. The flavor was Smokey-ish, but could have used some more natural wood smoke flavor. Reasonable price for the portion! Definitely worth a stop if you’re in the neighborhood.
nice place 100% recomended
Truly enjoyed my meal. The collard greens and smoked wings are my absolute favorite.
Feel free to steal there sauces cause their worth it !!!
Good food, staff really rude.
Great BBQ spot in the area!

Kenny's is a must when visiting DC. I found it by accident but now seek it out on return visits to the area. I immediately fell for the atmosphere and THEN they served me up their brisket sandwich. I've visited twice more since and food has been consistently amazing. You're going to get tender and juicy brisket (which I was just told is patiently smoked for 13 hours). That will not be outdone by the pulled pork. No sauce needed. It's THAT delicious, but if you need to mix your flavors, I recommend the Miss Honey sauce. This visit I went with a special, the bulgogi with a side of kimchi. If my taste buds could jump off my tongue and dance, they would be tap dancing on the beautiful wood benches and tables. So stop reading and get over to Kenny's to see for yourself. Sit outside on the patio. Sip on something from their tab. Try something, ANYTHING off their menu. You will not be disappointed. P.S. Take some home to your gf. She'll love ya for it!
This food was absolutely amazing! Headed back next week! 😊😊
It was terrible

Absolutely fantastic barbeque (cornbread was particularly delicious too), great prices, great area, good serving sizes, and right by capitol hill! Definitely a must-visit spot if you're looking for great yet (very) affordable food in D.C.!
Kennys bbq is unbeatable The people working there the cleanliness and most importantly food is awesome!!

If you remember the old Kenny's but haven't been in awhile, stop in. This is a great neighborhood spot with delicious food and ample outdoor seating. But what I love about Kenny's is their desire to be a true part of the community. This weekend we held a block party and on a whim reached out to Kenny's to see if they would be interested in donating some food. Not only did they donate, they went above and beyond by providing us with an incredible spread. The owner even made some homemade items not on their menu. They dropped it off and even came back to join in the festivities. As our neighborhood continues to change and as new business come in, it is heartening to know that there are still folks who have interest in on just serving the community but being active participants in it. Bravo, Kenny's. You have earned some customers for life!

Not too fond of the new owner but I think it’s great that they kept the old staff, it’s nice to see a friendly familiar face. I love the smoked chicken wings. I wish they still had the pulled chicken sandwich, it was so delicious.
Friendly Service, Quaint Atmosphere, Excellent Chicken Selection

Way too pricey... & the cornbread was cold, hard, and flavorless. Red beans & rice very dry. Onion rings soft and greasy. I got my food to go and didn't receive eating utensils. I could name at least 15 other bbq spots I'd rather spend my money on.👎
The Smoke Chicken wings were good the French fries could have been a little better.
Pull pork sandwiches were delicious but there was something in the restaurant that smelled weird and they were playing Loud Awful Music but Mmmmm that sauce was good.
Good tasting food and friendly staff.
Awesome food good customer service and many barbecue sauces to choose. The half chicken was perfect and I love the potato salad
Amazing food, prices, service, atmosphere. Its been locally owned for 20 years and it has a real authentic feel too it in a very built up corporate area. Highly recommend it and cant wait to go back!
The ribs are so good! But without a doubt the best thing is their sauce, in combination with the different complements that they sell! The price I saw very well the truth and luxury attention!

Cornbread and collard greens were amazing, brisket was fatty and juicy the way I prefer but needed bbq sauce for decent flavor. I like my brisket with a more smoky flavor than these, but there was some smokyness on the ends, it just didn't make it through the brisket meat. The Mac n cheese was okay-- I'm very particular about my Mac n cheese, so for me, it was nothing special. I tried 3 sauces (miss honey, Kenny's mild, and Kansas City). I loved the Kansas City bbq sauce. I think it will depend on your taste/preference. The service was not that great.. which is why I gave it 3 rather than 4 stars.
Decent food, pretty unclean inside. Think we had hairs in our food.
If you are not from the South you might think is ok BBQ.

I really enjoyed Kenny's BBQ Smokehouse.  I went for a late lunch with coworkers and grazed from each others portion.  The ribs were a little tough.  The macaroni and cheese saved the day, though!  Cheddar makes it all better.  And baked - thank you!The collard greens aren't grandma's BUT WHO'S IS??  The hunk of love that is the corn bread....think 'LIFE' The Movie.  Thick, hunk of just sweet enough goodness.  Yams were missing a little brown sugar, vanilla, butter and cinnamon but they were good none the less.  I had a taste for BBQ chicken but a half chicken is just too much portion for one so I opted or the fried flounder.  Battered, crispy, hot out of the fryer and seasoned well.  We didn't quite finish the reds beans and rice - kinda firm for everyone's liking.  A little out of place for a BBQ joint, too.  4 stars!

Happened upon this place and so glad we did.  In a great neighborhood, nice little BBQ place.  Come ready to eat as they give you a hefty portion.  Great find, a little it if our way, but glad we ventured out.

This place may be enjoyed by others, but the two times I have been here have been sub-par. I may be biased because I grew up eating quality BBQ in Georgia and North Florida.  First, the inside is small and dark, and the process for ordering is unclear. There's usually only two people working, so it doesn't make sense that the person taking the orders at the register is also responsible for bringing out all the trays of food outside. But because there isn't a counter to set the trays and call orsers, there aren't any other options.  Second, the BBQ sauces are incredibly disappointing. They have 5 or 6, and none of them enhance the meat's flavor. Also, both times I have visited I have to walk around to several tables in order to get a bottle of each sauce. The owners should really put a set of all the sauces at each table.  Third, the meat itself is bland. The ribs are tough and the pork sandwich made me feel sick.  The sides are just okay. The sweet potatoes are the best thing thing going for them.  Kenny's is in a good location, so it's really disappointing how unenjoyable it has been, especially after the new ownership.
Love their dry rub ribs

[2018] much better since the new owners took over.  sides are good, especially the baked beans.  Went back last week, the beans are a bit different.  Collards are now my favorite sides.  Cornbread was very good also.  The ribs just finished cooking when we got there on a Sunday around 4pm. They were outstanding.
Pretty good barbecue and sides.  Was very hot inside so we sat outside.
Great, authentic bbq. Not huge choice but good, honest food complemented by a variety of sauces and sides.

Well this place is pretty cool. I love that its in a neighborhood so you get a relaxing feel when sitting outside on the patio. The service was good, now for the food. The pork ribs were really good. The wings were ok. The yams and the potato salad were great. The brisket however was very disappointing. I also wasn't a fan of the watery sauces.
Good brisket
Love their BBQ ribs super delicious 😋
Ribs are good.  Mac & Cheese is not.

It was a super hot and humid day and they had the doors open and no a/c. We planned to eat inside to cool off from a day out and about, but no luck. The food was ok but nothing stood out. The macaroni and cheese was dry looking, as though it was from the previous day. The onion rings were very good and the chicken and ribs were good. Just nothing exceptional. We'll try it again in case we just caught them on an off day.
You get your monies worth. Check your order before leaving to make sure everything is as ordered. The cashier/waitress is excellent.

We had our first dining out experience in DC on Sunday night the waitress could not have been more rude. After asking what she would recommend she informed us to look at the menu and choose. She became angry when someone asked for water. Every question we asked her she snapped at us. She was very friendly to a couple of her friends that showed up. The woman whom I think was the owner came out and apologised for advertising that beer was available. It seemed they had problems with their licence. I'd suggest the owner hire friendlier staff. Food was okay and well priced.
This is the best place to eat BBQ in DC. I’ve tried all the menu items and each dish was delicious. Outdoor patio is very spacious and staff if super friendly! Definitely recommend trying it!
Amazing BBQ. Best place in Washington DC. Great atmosphere and amazing people. Perfect place to bring your date
My favorite bbq spot in dc.. definitely will be coming back. Everything on the menu was great.. highly recommended

This was my favorite bbq spot. New ownership makes for new changes. The bbq rib wasn't seasoned other than having the smoke flavor. Minced or pulled pork just not the same. They were out of the mild sauce and nothing else worked for me.  We decided that this was it for us. Our favorite catering go to is not the same. Good luck
Great food, but prices are REALLY high. Crowded at times, so service can be a bit slow. If I was rating it on the food alone, it would be a 5.

Love this place! Brisket is my favorite and the pulled pork is also delicious. All of the sides are good but I really like the mac n cheese, onion rings, and coleslaw. You really can't go wrong with anything on the menu!
Loved this place until new management took over. Portions got smaller and of course the prices went up. The food now is very hit or miss now. But at least some of the amazing staff is still there.
Saints going there for years another great estate sale
Very nice and busy and good food

We have only recently started going to Kenny’s. Honestly, I wasn’t expecting to like it but I’ve been pleasantly surprised by how tasty it is! I get a pulled pork sandwich and mac and cheese on the side. When I need soul food, it’s become my go to place.

Incredibly mediocre.  Brisket was dry as hell and it was a struggle chewing through it.  As a Missouri boy, this just pales in comparison to the places I've tried in KC and STL.  Yes, I know that's a high bar to set, but come on.

I love Kenny's BBQ so much! Thank you so much. I am so glad I started going there this month. Their  BBQ is so delicious. Their sides are so delicious. The collard greens are a little spicier than they should be, and I wish they would get rid of the stems, because they are not supposed to be there when you're making me really good collard greens, but yet they are still good.  I went to another famous place off of Eastern Avenue on the Maryland side and their sides were disgusting.  Their ribs are very good but their sides are not and I am so thankful to a place like Kenny's that not only makes delicious ribs but delicious side toppings.  Their macaroni and cheese is to die for. Everybody's macaroni and cheese is not good, theirs is.  They do need to work on their candied yams also because there is not enough sugar or butter or molasses in them and that is not good.  We can work with their candied yams, and we can doctor them up and make them better by putting a bunch of butter and sugar on them, but they should try a little bit harder on them and the collard greens.  I like their sweet Mississippi sauce also. It is delicious.  I've been three times so far this month.
Great brisket.

I love this place so much. I appreciate it more and more everyday. Their food is so delicious.  I went to another famous rib place off of Eastern avenue on the Maryland of Sherrif Rd. Their ribs were good, but their sides were so nasty, tasteless, and disgusting that they made me appreciate Kenny's even more.  I had some Kenny's sides from 5 days before leftover and I ate it with those ribs and it was just as delicious as if I had just bought Kenny sides that day.  I hate to say it but it was actually worth it for me to pay twice as much for Kenny sides then it is to save the money and have some nasty sides like that.  I have been there twice so far and I can't wait to come back again. We get the ribs plate every time and they are worth it to me.  There are no strong complaints here other than the collard greens are a little spicy but they calm down after a while. They need to get rid of them the stalks on the end.  They do not and they should not be cooking with them. They should have been cleaned off of the leaves.  They need more butter and sugar on the candied yams so that they can actually taste like candied yams are really truly supposed to taste like.

I love this place! A friendly atmosphere, and great service. The BBQ is delicious 😋 and super juicy, and flavorful. My favorite is the brisket - it melts in your mouth. I would highly recommend this restaurant! Five stars ⭐️ I’ll be back very soon.
A bit pricey but this is really good bbq with great service, a great dining room and outdoor picnic benches.
Not trying to be a bad person, but I know it should not taken way over 50mins to recd my order. I hope it's not one of those establishments.😏😏😏😏😏. Er
Excellent!

When i was 19, used to work there when it first opened and it was called Hogs on the Hill. The upstairs was a dine-in restaurant and the downstairs was for ordering take out where I was a cashier.  I've been loving the pork ribs since day one. I'm now 51 and eventhough i now live in Baltimore, MD, i still come to Washington, DC to pick up an order if ribs to go every 6 months.

What happened? I lived on Capital Hill a few years ago and Kennys was awesome. Now however, the ribs were more like beef jerky. It seems that the original owner sold the business but not for the better. You can redecorate the restaurant but if your food isnt good, then that's a huge problem. Hope it gets better.

Kenny's BBQ was amazing! The brisket was incredibly tender and juicy. Yams were a little on the sweeter side but still good nonetheless. They have a few sauces for you to choose from, Kenny's hot sauce was legit. Definitely a must stop again!

Kenny's, great place, I'd go there for the smell alone....only in DC for five days, luckily for me I was only staying round the corner so I made a b line for the place. Good vibe to Kenny's, popular with locals. Pulled Pork did it for me, that and the people who work there....Steve from Liverpool sends his regards..
Go there. Stop whatever you are doing and go.
Fantastic barbecue. Outdoor seating is lovely. Couldn’t leave anything on my plate. Very friendly service. Highly recommend while on Capitol Hill.
The place rules! Awesome BBQ! A real hidden gem in Capitol Hill

The food was very good! I got the fried trout and the pulled pork meals. They were fantastic!! I had potato salad, yams, collards, and mac&chz. I liked all the sides, but the yams and mac could use some improvement. I say that because being someone who's tasted a variety of soul food, I expect those sweet candied yams and cheesy macaroni. I wish I would've taken pics!! Funny thing is I've lived in DC my whole life, and yday was my first time going here. I really wished I went here under the old management b4 2017.
I'm so full right now. Excellent choice for all barbecue connoisseurs.

Long time customer, visited recently, sadly disappointed. What had been a genuine DC institution is now a cookie-cutter faux rustic "BBQ" joint down to the ubiquitous tin serving trays. The pork bbq sandwich was cold and flavorless as were the collard greens. The sauces were replaced with bland, institutional bottles. Good reasonably priced non-boutique barbecue has become harder and harder to find in this area, and while I'll give it another try, I'll recommend heading out to Southern Maryland or making the drive out to Warrenton, VA's BBQ Country for the real deal. Here's hoping Kenny's remembers what made it notable.  2/22/19. Went back for another try last week. Just as tired as before. That was it for me.

This bums me out because I really, really wanted to like this place. It is the only restaurant in the neighborhood, but unfortunately it’s location is about the only good thing. NEVER in my life have I had to throw away brisket because it was so tough, and I got the “fatty” cut brisket. The sides were good, but the service was horrible, the lady working the front acted so inconvenienced from taking my order. I can handle bad service and high prices, but “fatty” brisket that was so tough it was inedible? Unforgivable.

There is a great selection of fine drinks to choose from. The specials change randomly but they always have some interesting cuisine that is made to target local customers. It's a quaint small place, but kind of a big deal.

I visited Kenny's BBQ yesterday and I was so disappointed. The prices are pretty high for BBQ and I normally don't mind spending. However, on top of that the food was just disgusting, no sauce on the pulled pork, no seasoning the meat was not tender, potato salad watery and no taste, ribs were hard and no seasoning on the ribs.  Red rice & beans were hard, brisket dry & no taste. I was so disappointed and the girl who states she has been there for 18 years, has no customer service skills and not very knowledgeable.

I no longer feel welcomed here! The new management is appealing to a "frat boy" crowd! Amazingly they've taken the soul out of soul food!! Brothers and sisters go where you're celebrated, not tolerated!!! Go to Famous Daves.

Best BBQ Food my Family and i Have had! I definitely recommend this place!
I love the food. You can just test the ribs ❤❤❤❤ so quick and fast 10 ou 15 min at last. I.love you guys

Excellent food and friendly staff. Ordered the brisket and really enjoyed it. I would highly recommend for any BBQ fan in the area. I will definitely be back.
Love it. Great change from the old Kenny's. Could use some veggies for the kids. Great sauce selection.

If you're torn on the issue of gentrification, you're torn on Kenny's BBQ. It's been a local, hole-in-wall BBQ joint for years. It did one thing right- make good BBQ. The rest (atmosphere, cleanliness, etc) didn't matter. It was a classic. President Obama visited. It was a hidden gem.  Fast forward to 2017. There's new ownership. The neighborhood is changing. Hipsters are moving in and want the illusion of eating at a dive, but they want it their way. It must be a dive so they feel cool but it must be clean, 5 stars on Yelp, and have a cute sign to Instagram.  With all that in mind, Kenny's BBQ has been "hipsterized." I don't wear skinny jeans, but perhaps my "yuppieness" still puts me in the same category. I'm a fan! Here's why it will become the hipster spot of Capitol Hill:  1) The sign- The old red, cheesy sign has been replaced with a black one that says "Kenny's" in a cool, simple type font painted on the building. It looks good on Instagram.  2) The look and feel- Yes, it has a new brand. There are several outdoor high top tables. The inside is a clean, simple BBQ joint similar to what you'd expect in Austin, Texas. It's dark, but not overwhelming. There's window seating. There's perfect lighting in the corners. There's an open kitchen area. There's a typewriter (Yep, hipsters love a good typewriter) and a blown up photo of President Obama dining there. The menu is handwritten on parchment paper. You just feel cool being there.  3) The food- Hipsterized Kenny's is a classic example of the power of branding. It's literally the same food as before but with a new look and presentation; it tastes better. The brisket is perfect. The pulled pork tender in the right ways. The sides are on fleek (Especially the mac and cheese and MAYO based coleslaw).  4) The beer- What kind of beer do hipsters think they like? CRAFT beer! On tap or in a bottle, they serve local and regional craft beer.  5) The sauce- In the middle of the restaurant, there exists a wooden island with bottle after bottle of BBQ sauce and hot sauce. Of course they come in squeeze bottles so it doesn't look like they're trying too hard to be cool (so hipster). If you want Carolina BBQ (my recommendation), they have it. If you need mild, it's there along with 3-4 other BBQ options. Although different, they all pop with flavor.  Hipsters, grab your Warby Parkers and little dogs and smoother your half shaven face with some of the best BBQ in the District (and look cool doing it).
